# Sequencing Data

## Overview
This repository contains processed sequencing information associated with the undergraduate research project:

**Incidence and Genetic Risk Contribution of the PDX1 E224K Mutation in Type 2 Diabetes in Sri Lanka**

## Sequencing Platform
- Method: Sanger Sequencing
- Target Gene: PDX1
- Variant Investigated: E224K (c.670G>A)
- DNA Source: Human genomic DNA
- Study Design: Pilot case–control study

## Samples
- Type 2 Diabetes cases: 6
- Healthy controls: 7
- Total sequenced samples: 13

## Laboratory Workflow
1. Genomic DNA extraction
2. PCR amplification of the PDX1 target region
3. PCR product purification
4. BigDye Terminator Cycle Sequencing
5. Capillary electrophoresis using the SeqStudio Genetic Analyzer
6. Chromatogram quality assessment
7. Sequence alignment and mutation analysis

## Data Included
- Sequence alignments
- Mutation screening summary
- Processed variant analysis
- Figures used in the thesis

## Results
No PDX1 E224K (c.670G>A) mutation was detected in the sequenced samples included in this pilot study.

## Ethical Statement
No personally identifiable participant information is included in this repository. All data have been anonymized.

